2. Scan all non-empty rows in RNM for duplicate `(B,C)` keys and print counts/sums, plus corresponding rows in desired outcome.
3. Rewrite `RNM` data rows to unique rows, keeping first occurrence order and replacing col J with group sum; clear remaining old rows below.
